    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-20T00:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-18T17:00:00-05:00" n="275"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 883.00/52</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Diplomatic Agent at Cairo</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AO1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Arnold</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Cairo</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                        calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-12-20T00:30:00-05:00"
                        notBefore="1914-12-19T00:00:00+02:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                    </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 20, 1914, 12:30 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>To-day <persName>Prince Hussein</persName> was proclaimed Sultan of Egypt by
                        <persName corresp="#p_GV1">King George</persName>.</p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">Extract from the British note to <persName>Prince
                            Hussein</persName>
                    </hi>
                </p>
                <p>As regards foreign relations His Majesty’s Government deem it most consistent
                    with the new responsibilities assumed by Great Britain that the relations
                    between Your Highness’s Government and the representatives of foreign powers
                    should henceforth be conducted through His Majesty’s representative in
                    Cairo.</p>
                <p>His Majesty’s Government have repeatedly placed on record that the system of
                    treaties known as the capitulations by which Your Highness’s Government is bound
                    are no longer in harmony with the development of the country but in the opinion
                    of His Majesty’s Government the revision of those treaties may most conveniently
                    be postponed until the end of the present war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AO1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Arnold</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
